 the site please contact teal pennebaker tealpenn at stanford dot edu the initial meeting included a brief background presentation on timely policy issues followed by a discussion of lessons from other industries about achieving incentive compatible pricing most of the meeting was evoted to an exercise in which attendees adopted roles to play in negotiations between a series of stakeholders in a hospital payment reform discussion contact alan m garber search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
